35. Saturno rege: Saturnus = Kronos was an early equatiou in the Hel· lenization oi Italic mythology. One of the most notable features ol the legend os the Ages was the association of it with the great dynastia change os Olympos. The Golden Age was under the sway ol Kronos. Since then his son Zeus has ruled the world in his stead. This primitive association ol Kronos-Saturnus with the Golden Age persisted until a iate date, not only in the genuine follr tradition to which it really belongs, but also to a large extent in the literature, hence the frequency os such designations ior it as ἡ Κρόνον βασίλεια (Plato, Polit. 276 A), Saturno rege, as here, Saturnia regna (Verg. E. 4, 6), cp. aureus Saturnus (Verg. G. 2, 538), etc.
